{
  "texts": [
    "Upon lowering θ, more neurons are permitted to activate, so those participating in the denser, more weakly stored PP encoding should become active as well.",
    "Because our neurons are binary, active neurons in either the MF or the PP encoding would have the same activity level of 1, even though their connectivity strengths differ.",
    "This combined activity of both encodings is almost the same as the PP encoding alone, which contains many more active neurons.",
    "Thus, we expect the network to approximately retrieve the PP encoding at low θ.",
    "Figure 3 D -G illustrates the central behavior of our CA3 model; see Supplementary Fig. 3A, B for trouser and coat visualizations, which behave similarly to the sneaker visualizations shown here."
  ]
}